==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tau
<hw>Tau</hw> <pr>(tou)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>tay^</grk>.]</ety> <def>The nineteenth letter (⟦TAU⟧, ⟦tau⟧) of the
Greek alphabet, equivalent to English <it>t</it>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tau</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tau
<hw>Tau</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>tay^</grk> the
letter ⟦tau⟧ (English <er>T</er>).]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The
common American toadfish; -- so called from a marking resembling the
Greek letter <ex>tau</ex> (⟦tau⟧).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Tau cross</b></col>. <cd>See <xex>Illust.</xex> 6, of
<er>Cross</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Taught</ent>⟦br⟧
